toolSpecification.description:
Read and analyze code files. For small files (<10k chars), returns full content. For larger files, uses AST parsing to extract signatures.

IMPORTANT: Prefer this tool over readFile for code files unless you need specific line ranges. This tool intelligently handles file size and provides structured code analysis.

CORE FEATURES:
вҖў Auto-detects file size and chooses best approach
вҖў Small files: Returns complete file content
вҖў Large files: Extracts function/class signatures via AST
вҖў Fuzzy search for symbols (classes, functions, methods)
вҖў Scoped method search (Class.method syntax)
вҖў Supports: classes, functions, methods, arrow functions, generators

BEHAVIOR:
вҖў File <10k chars: Returns full file content (selector ignored)
вҖў File вүҘ10k chars + no selector: Returns all signatures
вҖў File вүҘ10k chars + selector: Searches for selector, shows implementation
вҖў Directory: Returns signatures from code files

SUPPORTED PATTERNS:
вҖў Traditional functions: function foo() {}
вҖў Arrow functions: const foo = () => {}
вҖў Async functions: async function foo() {}, const foo = async () => {}
вҖў Generator functions: function* foo() {}, *methodName() {}, async *methodName() {}
вҖў Class properties with arrow functions: filter = (x) => x
вҖў Getters/setters: get status() {}, set status(v) {}
вҖў Abstract classes: abstract class Base {}
вҖў Nested classes: class Outer { static Inner = class {} }
вҖў Enums: enum Status { Active, Inactive }
вҖў Namespaces: namespace Utils { export class Helper {} }
вҖў Interfaces: interface IData { method(): void }
вҖў Class methods and constructors
вҖў Scoped lookup: ClassName.methodName (single-level only, e.g., MyClass.method)

NOTE: Use readFile with line ranges for not supported patterns.

